&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are launching our brand new paediatric same day emergency care service in the Royal London Hospital and are looking for dynamic, experienced nurses to join our team. SDEC provides an alternative pathway for children and young people who require care from the specialist paediatric teams without the need for admission to hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be dynamic, motivated and able to juggle multiple competing priorities in a fast paced environment. You will have experience of rapid assessment of babies, children and young people and be a competent and confident communicator with the multi disciplinary team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service will be operational from 09.45am until 10.15pm 7 days a week and welcome applications from those seeking both full and part time employment. The posts are initially funded as 6 month fixed term contracts but we would be particularly interested in hearing from candidates who may be interested in a secondment from their host organisation or department. Please ensure you discuss your application with your line manager to avoid disappointment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Jo Conroy - General Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;jo.conroy2@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
